  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of Humanitarian Air Service in the Kasai</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Deployment of a Helicopter in Kasai Region by UNHAS DRC to facilitate increased humanitarian needs in the region.

The humanitarian situation in the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC) has deteriorated dramatically over the last year. The crisis has deepened, affecting people in areas previously considered stable such as the Kasais.  According to OCHA, renewed conflict has forced more than 1.5 million to flee their homes in 2017, an average of 6000 people per day. Today, there are over 3.9 million internally displaced people, currently the highest number in Africa.

Resources from CHF will be used to provide air services to the humanitarian community in the Kasais . The funds will be critical in ensuring that WFP is able to maintain enhanced air services particularly in areas of greatest humanitarian need that are not accessible by fixed wing aircraft in  the Kasais.</narrative>
  </description>
